The Kano State Fire Service has confirmed the death of a 20-year-old man, Anas Idris, who drowned in open waters at Jan Dutse, Tudun Wada Local Government Area. Saminu Abdullahi, Spokesman of the Kano State Fire Service, said the incident occurred on Friday morning. “We received an emergency call at about 08:20am from one Kabiru Sarkin Jan-Duste and we dispatched our rescue team to the scene at about 8:26a.m,’’ he said. He added that the victim was rescued unconscious and later confirmed dead. Abdullahi said his corpse was later handed over to the Jan Dutse village head, Kabiru Sarki. “The cause of the incident was as a result of local swimming,” he said. In another development, he said the Fire Service received an emergency call on Friday morning at about 07:55am from one Magani Muhammed-Inuwa, that a 14-year-old boy, Usman Magaji, has drowned as he swam in open water at Mariri Farawa behind the police station in Kumbotso Local Government Area. He said we quickly dispatched our rescue team to the scene at about 08:11 a.m. Abdullahi said the victim was brought out dead from the open water and his corpse was handed over to Inspector Aliyu Umar of the Farawa police station,